definitions: To drop or let fall in a mass.
To deposit or leave in a careless or untidy way.
To get rid of something unwanted, often by discarding it.
To end a romantic relationship with someone.
To transfer data from one place to another, often from memory to a storage device.
examples: He dumps his dirty clothes on the floor.
The company dumps its waste illegally.
She dumps him after a short argument.
The programmer dumps the log file to the console.
